Code optimization

Best practices

Readability improvements

ğŸ“¦ Clean and modular backend with RESTful API

ğŸŒ Environment variable support for secure API key integration

ğŸ§ª Tech Stack
Frontend: React.js, Tailwind CSS, PrismJS, React Simple Code Editor

Backend: Node.js, Express.js

AI: Google Gemini API (gemini-2.0-flash)

Hosting Ready: Easily deployable to platforms like Render, Vercel, or Heroku

ğŸ”‘ How It Works
The user writes or pastes JavaScript code into the editor.

On clicking "Review", the code is sent to the backend via Axios.

The backend forwards the code as a prompt to the Gemini LLM.

The LLM returns a natural language review, which is rendered on the UI using Markdown.

